Class TextDataFileParser

java.lang.Object
  gov.nasa.ial.mde.io.TextDataFileParser
All Implemented Interfaces:
FileParser
Direct Known Subclasses:
ExpressionFileParser
public class TextDataFileParser
extends Object
implements FileParser

The TextDataFileParser will parse a text data file with an optional text header describing each column of data and with the data arranged rows and columns. The result of parsing the text data file is a List of AnalyzedData items where each entry in the List corresponds to one segment of data and where each segment corresponds to the chunk of data between a gaps in the values in the first column of data. The TextDataFileParser will analyze the text data file to determine what character is consistently used as a delimiter between columns of data. This allows the TextDataFileParser to parse most any text data file provided that the delimiter is consistently used throughout the file.

The TextDataFileParser can also read text data files in the Comma Separated Values (CSV) format, which is compatible with the CSV file format used by Microsoft Excel.

Here is how the TextDataFileParser works:

  1. The text data file must have at least two columns.
  2. If a text header is exists, the number of columns in the text headers must match the number of columns for the data.
  3. It will skip blank lines in the header and data fields.
  4. If a data cell is empty (for a given row and column, nothing is specified but there are valid delimiters) it will use a value of 0.0 for it.
  5. The first column of data must be in ascending order.
  6. Duplicate entries in the first column of data are allowed.
  7. If the gap between first column data values is greater than 2 times the average difference between the values then a new segment of data is created.
